<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[In the mortar, make a paste with chopped green chilies, grated ginger, crushed nuts, coriander seeds, cumin seeds, fennel seeds. When crushed, dilute with water. Or just use a food processor.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Make a cross cut at the bottom of the tomatoes, soak in boiling water a couple of minutes, then rinse in fresh water and peel.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Fry the spice paste in ghee or oil / butter mixture over medium high heat until it dries out a bit.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Chop the tomatoes and add them to the spices. Cook 3-4 mins]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Add the zucchini, turmeric, salt, and first lot of chopped coriander and lower heat. Cook on low heat 10 - 15 mins, stirring occasionally and adding water if it gets too dry.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Add remaining chopped herbs and serve]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
